alerts.title: Winter Weather Advisory
alerts.description:
...SNOW EXPECTED THROUGH WEDNESDAY ESPECIALLY IN THE SNOWBELT...
.Low pressure will continue to track through the Ohio Valley
tonight with snow affecting much of the area. Heaviest amounts of
snow overnight will occur in the lakeshore counties adjacent to
Lake Erie, with snow tapering off across the western part of the
forecast area by Tuesday morning.
The low pressure will move to the east coast and become a major
east coast snow storm on Tuesday. Our snow will transition to
lake effect snow across northeast Ohio and northwest Pennsylvania
Tuesday afternoon and continue into Wednesday.
Strong and gusty north winds will become northwest by Wednesday
with blowing and drifting snow.
...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM EDT
TUESDAY...
* Accumulations...Additional snowfall of 1 to 2 inches overnight,
bringing storm total snowfall amounts of 2 to 5 inches.
* Timing...Snow will continue into early Tuesday morning before
tapering to scattered snow showers and flurries.
* Impacts...Untreated roads will be snow covered with reduced
visibility at times. Blowing and drifting snow will develop.
* Winds...North increasing to 15 to 25 mph with gusts of 35 mph.
* Temperatures...Falling into the teens to low 20s overnight.
